      <li>CSS, Sass</li>
      <li>Bootstrap</li>
      <li>Photoshop</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <section id="portfolio">
    <h2>Sample work:</h2>
    <div>
    <% projects.forEach(function(project) { %>
      <div class="project">
        <h3><%= project.title %></h3>
        <h4><%= project.tech %></h4>
        <a href="<%= project.img_url %>">
          <img src="/images/<%= project.img %>" alt="screenshot"/>
        </a>
        <p><%= project.description %></p>
        <ul>
          <% project.links.forEach(function(link) { %>
          <li><a href="<%= link.url %>"><%= link.name %></a></li>
          <% }); %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    <% }); %>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section id="about">
    <h2>About Me:</h2>
    <p>I'm excited to begin a new career in a field where I'll always be learning and growing!</p>
    <p>After several years of making websites as a hobby, I enrolled at <a href="http://launchschool.com">LaunchSchool.com</a>, a remote learning program which emphasizes mastery-based learning and fundamentals. Besides scheduling concerns, I chose this program because I wanted to really understand what was going on in my code. I completed Launch School's core curriculum in 18 months and appreciated the chance to dig into details such as variable scopes, closures, regular expressions, object creation patterns, "this", and more.</p>
    <p>Since then, I've explored several frameworks including Ruby on Rails, Vue.js, and Express.js. I'm excited to continue learning about these tools and/or others, and I'm eager to work together with other developers on a great project.</p>
  </section>
